description.narrative: Through sustained evidenced based lifesaving communication, community engagement and participation programming, UNICEF engaged with men, women, boys and girls through 393,738 households to promote positive social and behavior change for children in South Sudan. In collaboration with South Sudan Council of Churches, Islamic Council and WFP, UNICEF launched UNICEF's global faith-based initiative promoting child rights. Around 60 religious' leaders pledged to mainstream the positive social change for children and to advocate for ending child marriage. UNICEF continued to co-lead the Risk Communication, Social Mobilization and Community Engagement technical working group under the National Ebola virus disease (EVD) Task Force. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
